Fix the following files in /tmp/sv-db2e0fdc972049d7ab625172c4a0107d/before to resolve IL trim/AOT warnings. Do NOT use `#pragma warning disable` or `[UnconditionalSuppressMessage]`.

## 1. ArmOperation.cs

Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)]` to ALL `T` type parameters in this file.

The methods are:
- `Rehydrate<T>` (line 44) - public, has `where T : notnull` constraint
- `RehydrateAsync<T>` (line 82) - public, has `where T : notnull` constraint
- `IsResource<T>` (line 96) - private static, has `where T : notnull` constraint

Add `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` to the usings if not already present.

The syntax should be:
```csharp
public static ArmOperation<T> Rehydrate<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T>(ArmClient client, RehydrationToken rehydrationToken, ArmClientOptions options = null) where T : notnull
```

Apply the same pattern to all three methods.

## 2. GenericOperationSource.cs

Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)]` to the `T` type parameter of the class definition.

Current: `internal class GenericOperationSource<T> : IOperationSource<T>`
After: `internal class GenericOperationSource<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T> : IOperationSource<T>`

The file already has `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;`.

## 3. ArmClientBuilderExtensions.cs

The method `AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>` at line 27-31 calls `builder.RegisterClientFactory<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions>(configuration)` which is marked with `[RequiresUnreferencedCode]` and `[RequiresDynamicCode]` in Azure.Core.

Add `[RequiresUnreferencedCode]` and `[RequiresDynamicCode]` attributes to this method.

The file already has `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;`.

```csharp
[RequiresUnreferencedCode("Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values is not supported with trimming. Use the Configuration Binder Source Generator (EnableConfigurationBindingGenerator=true) instead.")]
[RequiresDynamicCode("Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values requires generating dynamic code at runtime, for example instantiating generic types.")]
public static IAzureClientBuilder<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions> AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>(this TBuilder builder, TConfiguration configuration)
    where TBuilder : IAzureClientFactoryBuilderWithConfiguration<TConfiguration>
```

## 4. ArmEnvironment.cs

Replace line 80: `public override string ToString() => JsonSerializer.Serialize(this);`

With a manual JSON construction using Utf8JsonWriter to avoid JsonSerializer:

```csharp
public override string ToString()
{
    var buffer = new System.Buffers.ArrayBufferWriter<byte>();
    using (var writer = new Utf8JsonWriter(buffer))
    {
        writer.WriteStartObject();
        writer.WriteString("Endpoint", Endpoint?.ToString());
        writer.WriteString("Audience", Audience);
        writer.WriteString("DefaultScope", DefaultScope);
        writer.WriteEndObject();
    }
    return System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetString(buffer.WrittenSpan);
}
```

Remove `using System.Text.Json;` if no other code in the file uses it, but keep it if other System.Text.Json types are used. Actually, `Utf8JsonWriter` is in `System.Text.Json`, so keep the using.

## 5. ArmClientOptions.cs

Replace the `JsonSerializer.Deserialize<Dictionary<string, Dictionary<string, JsonElement>>>(span)` call on line 52 with direct `JsonDocument` parsing. 

Current code (lines 51-77):
```csharp
var span = BinaryData.FromStream(stream).ToMemory().Span;
var allProfile = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<Dictionary<string, Dictionary<string, JsonElement>>>(span);
var armProfile = allProfile["resource-manager"];
foreach (var keyValuePair in armProfile)
{
    var namespaceName = keyValuePair.Key;
    var element = keyValuePair.Value;
    // ... rest stays the same
```

Replace with:
```csharp
var span = BinaryData.FromStream(stream).ToMemory();
using var doc = JsonDocument.Parse(span);
var armProfile = doc.RootElement.GetProperty("resource-manager");
foreach (var keyValuePair in armProfile.EnumerateObject())
{
    var namespaceName = keyValuePair.Name;
    var element = keyValuePair.Value;
    // ... rest stays the same (element is already JsonElement, so EnumerateObject/EnumerateArray work)
```

Note: `BinaryData.FromStream(stream).ToMemory().Span` is used with `JsonSerializer.Deserialize<T>(ReadOnlySpan<byte>)`. When switching to `JsonDocument.Parse`, use `ReadOnlyMemory<byte>` (`.ToMemory()` without `.Span`), since `JsonDocument.Parse` accepts `ReadOnlyMemory<byte>`.

